items.name: Billions of Styles - Standalone, for style prompts
items.description:
This wildcards are a byproduct of my style study. You can use them to add random styles to your creations or just have a look at all the possibilities SD and all those awesome models give you. Keep in mind, that not all styles might be part of your favourite model. For an overview consult my GUIDE.

Don't forget to leave a ‚ù§Ô∏è to get a notification for future updates. ‚≠ê reviews are appreciated, too. Let me see what you created with this tool. ;)

note: Yaml files will throw isseus when using: "a1111-sd-webui-tagcomplete"extension. That's related to the extension, not the wildcards.

Usage

Unleash the full power:

Activate: Dynamic Prompts->Advanced Options->Unlink seed from prompt

Usage is pretty much the same as for "regular" wildcards.

You need the SD Dynamic Prompt Extension. Put the files directly into the wildcard folder:

~\stable-diffusion-webui\extensions\sd-dynamic-prompts\wildcards

They show up as a menu on the left in the Wildcards tab.

The YAML is structured and indented (that's how they work). Just with a little difference. You have to add the category layers in the wildcard.

Examples:

__BoStyles/random-anything__
__BoStyles/random-artstyle__
__BoStyles/random-punk-styles__
__BoStyles/random-atmosphere__
__BoStyles/random-rendering__
__BoStyles/random-graphic-engines__
__BoStyles/image-styles__
__BoStyles/image-techniques__
__BoStyles/random-depiction-styles__

A cool thing you can do, too, is using a wildcard "*" in the wildcards. So you could use the normal chararcter wildcards in the same prompt and get chars from both sets:

__BoStyles/*__ # for a random subset of the styles

Have a look what's in there, too. You'll find a full list below. You can use each subcategory separately.

You are welcome

Leave a star review, if you like it. so other can find those awesome cards more easily.

I plan to add more themes as extensions in the future. SDXL is coming, and wildcards are limitless.

If you want to support me, feel free to buy me a coffee. ;)

Have experimenting with it.

Anime Art Diffusion XL

Check the version description below (bottom right) for more info and add a ‚ù§Ô∏è to receive future updates.
Do you like what I do? Consider supporting me on Patreon üÖøÔ∏è to get exclusive tips and tutorials, or feel free to buy me a coffee ‚òï


Raising from the ashes of ArtDiffusionXL-alpha, this is the first anime oriented model I make for the XL architecture. It will serve as a good base for future anime character and styles loras or for better base models.

Should work well around 8-10 cfg scale and I suggest you don't use the SDXL refiner, but instead do a i2i step on the upscaled image (like highres fix).

It's trained on multiple famous artists from the anime sphere (so no stuff from Greg Rutkowsky, but stuff like Sam Yang and Wlop for example). The model is oriented at producing stylized results.
I also suggest you use words like 8k and high resolution because otherwise it tends to go too much low detail. Look at the examples.

Enjoy!

items.name: Kizuki - Alternative Checkpoint
items.description:
I have set up a Discord-Server where we can share images / ideas / prompts and help each other out. Also, if you have a LoRA request, feel free to ask me there.

If you want to support my work or gain early access / exclusive loras feel free to check out my Patreon or Ko-Fi.

Kizuki Alternative

I know that there are already a lot of 2D Anime Checkpoints out there and that is why I hesitated to post another one before. But with SD 1.5 coming to an end, I felt like it kind of doesn't matter anymore if there is one more out there^^. So yeah... I hope some of you will enjoy using it and feedback is always appreciated.

Prompts to get started

Prompt: best quality, masterpiece

Negative: (worst quality: 1.4), (low quality: 1.4), wet clothes

* Adjust the strength and prompts to your liking, but keep in mind that the negative prompts are very important!

** Use (nsfw:value) positive/negative prompt as needed.

Settings to use

Most samplers work pretty well, so try out what works for you and pick your favorite.

Also test how the different upscalers affect the checkpoint, as they make quite a difference.

My "personal" basic settings:

Sampler: DPM++ SDE Karras

Steps: 24

Clipskip: 2

CFG Scale: 10

VAE: Included in Checkpoint

HiRes fix: Latent / 4x-AnimeSharp

HiRes Steps: 12

HiRes Denoise: 20-49

Upscale by 1x for prompt or seed testing and higher for final results.

Embeddings:

items.name: MBBXL Ultimate
items.description:
The new version of MBBXL has been trained on >18000 training images in over 18000 steps. It's probably the most significant fine-tune of SDXL so far and the one that will give you noticeably different results from SDXL for every prompt.

The model tends towards a "magical realism" look, not quite photo-realistic but very clean and well defined.


Very flexible model that looks good with most prompts (including simple prompts).

Use of the SDXL Refiner is not recommended with this model. Shouldn't be needed either.

Recommended negative:
blurry, blurred detail, poorly hands, poorly face, enhanced hands, missing fingers, mutated hands, fused fingers, deformed, malformed limbs, disfigured, watermarked, text, extremely grainy, very chromatic aberration, oversaturated

Recommended settings: 1024x1024 or 1336x768.

DPM++ SDE 30 steps or more.

Works very well with hires.fix, try 768x768 upscaled to 2x!

Limitations:

Skin textures are not strong, to come later probably as an add-on lora.

modelVersions.name: v1.0RC
modelVersions.description:
Big update to the model, with an additional 135000 steps on 15000 training images.

The model is much more capable and very different from the base SDXL model (and also very different from all the other currently released SDXL fine tunes).

If you want a model that's actually fun to try out and compare with the SDXL base model, and not mostly the same, this is the model for you!

items.name: West Gark - Mayan/Aztec people fantasy by Paradigme
items.description:
"Like the Estarsitz, they are descendants of the now collapsed United Empire, and have only been able to retain a small part of their vast territory, a small island to the west called Krag Island. They are great individualists, and for them, life only has taste if it's made up of challenges. As a result, they usually leave their home region to go on adventures.

Adopting a tribal lifestyle, the Western Garks are divided into several clans with a strong shamanic component. Some of them live in hut encampments, while others live on the remains of ziggurats belonging to a past civilization. Easily recognized by their large body mass, they generally wear their trophies and obsidian weapons ostentatiously to show the respect due to them. Most of them worship Iracundus, god of war and blood."

-----------------------------------------

Here's an AI model that allows you to generate members of mayan/aztec fantasy. It was specifically designed to illustrate the west Garks, a people in my role-playing game universe "Landhelven."

I recommend using the trigger words "WestGark" and "warrior," but you can replace "warrior" with other professions.

I hope you enjoy using this model. Please feel free to provide feedback on its strengths and weaknesses.

If you'd like to support my creations, here's my Patreon page:
